1 agreements with owners of firearms who are voluntarily seeking to securely store
2 their firearms; now, therefore,
3
4 THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
5 SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
6
7 Section 1. Chapter 41 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
8 section to read as follows:
9 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, a licensed firearm dealer or
10 local law enforcement agency is immune from civil liability for any act or
11 omission arising from a firearm hold agreement, including, without limitation,
12 any personal injury or death which results after the return of any firearm to the
13 owner of the firearm at the termination of a firearm hold agreement.
14 2. A licensed firearm dealer or local law enforcement agency is not immune
15 from civil liability pursuant to subsection 1 if:
16 (a) An action arising from a firearm hold agreement was the result of gross
17 negligence or reckless or unlawful conduct on the part of the licensed firearm
18 dealer or local law enforcement agency; or
19 (b) The licensed firearm dealer or local law enforcement agency knew at the
20 time the person sought to retrieve a firearm pursuant to a firearm hold agreement
21 that the person was:
22 (1) Demonstrating behavior that the person would engage in the
23 unlawful use of the firearm;
24 (2) Demonstrating behavior that the person would cause harm to himself
25 or herself or another person; or
26 (3) Prohibited from owning, possessing or having under his or her
27 custody or control any firearm pursuant to NRS 202.360.
28 3. As used in this section:
29 (a) “Firearm hold agreement” means a written or oral agreement between
30 an owner of a firearm and a licensed firearm dealer or local law enforcement
31 agency in which a licensed firearm dealer or local law enforcement agency:
32 (1) Takes [physical] possession of the owner’s [lawfully possessed]
33 firearm at the request of the owner; and
34 (2) [Holds the firearm for an agreed upon period of not less than 21
35 days; and
36 (3)] Returns the firearm to the owner according to the terms of the
37 agreement.
38 (b) “Licensed firearm dealer” means a person licensed pursuant to 18 U.S.C.
39 § 923(a).
